main event: A silver object was observed over Moses Lake, Washington for 1.5 minutes by AEC employees.
interesting points: The object was silver in color and appeared to move in a straight line,No photographs were documented in the report,There was a weather balloon released from Yakima at the time, but the object was suspected to not be this balloon, An aircraft was in the area during the sighting, The sighting had an uncertain conclusion with suggestions of it being a balloon, aircraft, or astronomical object.
